The paper deals with the problem of autonomous navigation of Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs) in indoor environments, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves the use of a deep learning model, Convolutional Neural Network (ConvNet), to learn a controller strategy for the quadcopter, which requires computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the system through real-time experiments, which involves machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the system involves the integration of hardware and software components, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
